{% block content %}

<div class="container" style="padding: 20px;" >
    
    <h4 class="featurette-heading text-center"><img class="featurette-image text-center" src="{{ asset('Raptor/img/logo.png') }}" style="margin-right: 15px;" width="250"></h4>
    <h2 class="featurette-heading text-center"><span class="">Welcome to Raptor 2</span></h2>
    <hr>
    <br><br>
    <div class="featurette" style="background: transparent !important;">
            
            <p class="lead">
                
                In this version Raptor implements his logic under Slim micro framework, giving you a nice experience with a light core.
                We include a lot of new functions in this release like Interactive Guide, AOP(Aspect Oriented Programming) and other toys.<br><br>
                The gold of raptor always will be the cognitive charge reduction in the development, and give you a cool enviroment to
                do professional webs.<br><br>
                To start, look the requirements below and see your current state:<br>
                <table class="table">
                    <thead>
                        <th>Requirements</th>
                        <th>Value</th>
                    <thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr>
                            <td>PHP 5.4 > <span class="label label-danger">Required</span></td>
